body:
The linux one was built by using the following command:
```bash
python3 /onnxruntime_src/tools/ci_build/build.py --build_dir /build --config Release --skip_submodule_sync  --parallel --build_shared_lib --build_java --use_openmp --enable_onnx_tests && cd /build/Release && make install DESTDIR=/build/linux-x64
```
source: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/tools/ci_build/github/azure-pipelines/java-api-packaging-pipelines.yml

It should be fixed in master as part of the Apple Silicon changes. Test that out and see if it works (as I haven't got a Linux aarch64 machine to check it with).

You will need to compile it yourself, I don't know if the plan is to compile it for Linux and Mac aarch64 in the 1.6 release for Java.

@Craigacp Yes, that works fine, sorry I missed the changes on master. I can confirm it built fine on Linux ARM64 (tested on Amazon Linux 2 64-bit ARM AMI).

You commit covered the required changes to build, is there an issue to modify the packaging pipeline referenced above?

I don't think there is an issue to expand the binaries shipped to maven central.

@faxu @yuslepukhin are there any plans to include ARM binaries in the onnxruntime cpu jar? Or add a different jar with ARM binaries for Linux, macOS and Windows (though I don't know if anyone has checked Java on Windows ARM)?
We'll evaluate this for future releases. Closing the topic as the the original issue is resolved.

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I want to use ONNXRuntime on my node app. However, this app needs to be compatible with Linux on x64 and arm64.
This is an issue, since there's no prebuilt binary for arm64.
I would build my own binary, but it's unpractical for many reasons, one of them being electron-forge doesn't allow npm dependencies on local files.

**System information**
- ONNX Runtime version (you are using): "onnxruntime-node": "^1.8.0",

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I would like the ONNX releases to include a binary for Linux-arm64 like: `onnxruntime-linux-arm64-1.8.0.tgz`

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
A clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.
The alternative would be for me to create my own npm bindings for ONNX Runtime with the same `prebuild-install` script as yours, but including the binary that I need from a repository of my own. This is not ideal, since I would have to manage my own builds/releases.

Another alternative would be to fallback to source compile if no binaries were found.
Here's an example of this behavior when installing another package.
```
> lzma-native@6.0.1 install /home/adestech/default-speaker/node_modules/lzma-native
> node-pre-gyp install --fallback-to-build && rimraf build

node-pre-gyp WARN Using request for node-pre-gyp https download 
node-pre-gyp WARN Tried to download(404): https://node-pre-gyp.addaleax.net/lzma-native/lzma_native-v6.0.1-n-api-linux-arm64.tar.gz 
node-pre-gyp WARN Pre-built binaries not found for lzma-native@6.0.1 and node@12.14.1 (node-v72 ABI, glibc) (falling back to source compile with node-gyp)
```

**Additional context**
Add any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.

issue.body:
### Describe the feature request

I request Linux ARM builds for Java API (at least aarch64).

This feature was requested before in #6026 and #8176.

Currently JVM supports platforms like arm32 and aarch64, but lack of builds or platform support kills the future Java ML development.

### Describe scenario use case

I would like to use [Deep Java Learning Tensorflow](https://docs.djl.ai/engines/tensorflow/index.html) on aarch64 (and possibly arm32), but DJL depend on this project and needs the support for aarch64 platform here first.
